# Mastering JavaScript Async/Await Patterns

Async/await has revolutionized how we write asynchronous code in JavaScript. However, there are many patterns and best practices that can take your code to the next level...

## Error Handling Patterns

### 1. Try/Catch Blocks
```javascript
async function fetchData() {
  try {
    const response = await fetch('/api/data');
    const data = await response.json();
    return data;
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Fetch failed:', error);
    throw new Error('Data fetch failed');
  }
}
```

### 2. Error-First Pattern
```javascript
async function safeAsync(fn) {
  try {
    const result = await fn();
    return [result, null];
  } catch (error) {
    return [null, error];
  }
}
```

